t**\\n\\nI'm considering how the agent runs the JVM with H2Test first. It generates dynamic access from clinit and wonders if the user-code filter excludes the helper. Since the caller is org.h2, that could impact things. To be cautious, I think I should add a reflect-config for the h2.JdbcUtilsTest$PassThroughJavaObjectSerializer constructors. However, since there's no tests-only reflect config for native, I’ll need to add one to ensure everything works smoothly. It feels like I’m covering all bases!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ENkYOKRbsVI2FCnbCfw0IBnE|fc_0436d349b38d0e700169f1001ec6f88193bdc9ba13907a81a3", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n \"systemProperty|jvmArgs|tasks\\.test|test \\{\" tests/src -g build.gradle | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2409, "output": 1262, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34903, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777401869051, "responseId": "resp_0436d349b38d0e700169f1000d95808193887d3419924c2c8e"}}
